Package: variationalDCM
Type: Package
Title: performs variational Bayesian estimation for DCMs
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Keiichiro", "Hijikata", email = "", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Motonori", "Oka", role = "aut"),
    person("Kazuhiro", "Yamaguchi", role = "aut"),
    person("Kensuke", "Okada", role = "aut"))
Description: This package enables fast estimations by variational Bayesian methods for various DCMs and can be applied to large-scale data. We implement five functions that estimate model parameters for 1) deterministic input noisy AND gate (DINA) model, 2) saturated DCM, 3) multiple-choice DINA model, and 4) hidden Markov type longitudinal general DCM and estimates 5) Q-matrix for DINA model.
Depends: R (>= 4.2.2)
License: MIT
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: mvtnorm
